properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued December 31 at 7:26PM EST until January 1 at 12:00AM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...Up to one half foot of inundation above ground level in
low-lying areas near shorelines and tidal waterways.

* WHERE...Queen Anne's, Talbot, and Caroline Counties in Maryland.

* WHEN...Until midnight EST tonight.

* IMPACTS...Flooding is possible in and near Church Hill, Kent
Island, Saint Michaels, Denton, and other locations near the
bay, Choptank River, and other tidal tributaries.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT EST TONIGHT
